examples: to plank a floor or a ship

definitions.definition: To bake (fish, etc.) on a piece of cedar lumber.
To lay down, as on a plank or table; to stake or pay cash.
examples: to plank money in a wager

definitions.definition: To harden , as hat bodies , by felting .
To splice together the ends of slivers of wool , for subsequent drawing .
To pose for a photograph while lying rigid, face down, arms at side, in an unusual place.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To cover something with planking .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To bake (fish, etc.) on a piece of cedar lumber.
( transitive , colloquial ) To lay down, as on a plank or table; to stake or pay cash.
( transitive ) To harden , as hat bodies , by felting .
To splice together the ends of slivers of wool , for subsequent drawing .
( intransitive ) To pose for a photograph while lying rigid, face down, arms at side, in an unusual place.
